---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const title = "Preparing for Your First Behaviour Support Meeting | Syed Bokhari";
const description = "What to expect and how to prepare for your initial consultation with a behaviour support practitioner.";
const category = "First Meeting";
const date = "2025-12-28";
const readTime = "6 min read";
const tags = ["First Meeting", "Preparation", "What to Expect"];
const formattedDate = new Date(date).toLocaleDateString('en-AU', {
  year: 'numeric',
  month: 'long',
  day: 'numeric'
});
---

<BaseLayout title={title} pathname={Astro.url.pathname} description={description}>
  <!-- ARTICLE HEADER -->
  <article class="blog-post">
    <header class="article-header">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="article-meta">
          <span class="article-category">{category}</span>
          <span class="article-date">{formattedDate}</span>
          <span class="article-read-time">{readTime}</span>
        </div>
        
        <h1 class="article-title">Preparing for Your First Behaviour Support Meeting</h1>
        
        <div class="article-tags">
          {tags.map(tag => (
            <span class="tag">{tag}</span>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- ARTICLE CONTENT -->
    <div class="article-content">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="content-wrapper">
          <div class="post-content">
            <h2>Before the Meeting</h2>
            <p>Preparation is key to making the most of your initial consultation with a behaviour support practitioner. Here are some steps to help you prepare:</p>

            <h3>Gather Relevant Information</h3>
            <p>Collect and organize the following documents:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Current NDIS plan and goals</li>
              <li>Any existing behaviour support documentation</li>
              <li>Recent incident reports or support notes (if applicable)</li>
              <li>Contact details for key support people</li>
              <li>Relevant medical or psychological reports</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Think About Your Goals</h3>
            <p>Consider what you hope to achieve through behaviour support. What would success look like for you or your loved one? Think about:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>What behaviours are causing concern?</li>
              <li>When and where do these behaviours occur?</li>
              <li>What have you already tried?</li>
              <li>What outcomes are you hoping for?</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>During the Meeting</h2>
            <h3>What to Expect</h3>
            <p>Your initial consultation will typically include:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Discussion of current situation and challenges</li>
              <li>Review of any existing documentation</li>
              <li>Explanation of the behaviour support process</li>
              <li>Discussion of supervision arrangements (if applicable)</li>
              <li>Outline of next steps and timeline</li>
              <li>Opportunity for you to ask questions</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Questions to Ask</h3>
            <p>Prepare a list of questions, such as:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>What does the assessment process involve?</li>
              <li>How long does the process typically take?</li>
              <li>What are the costs involved?</li>
              <li>How will we measure progress?</li>
              <li>What is your availability and service area?</li>
              <li>How does supervision work (if applicable)?</li>
              <li>What will be expected of me and my support team?</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Share Your Story</h3>
            <p>Be prepared to share information about:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>What a typical day looks like</li>
              <li>Successful strategies you've used</li>
              <li>Challenges you face regularly</li>
              <li>What's most important to you</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Who Should Attend</h2>
            <p>Consider who should be present at the meeting:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>The NDIS participant (if appropriate)</li>
              <li>Family members or guardians</li>
              <li>Key support workers</li>
              <li>Service coordinator (if applicable)</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>After the Meeting</h2>
            <p>Take time to reflect on the discussion and whether you feel comfortable with the practitioner's approach. Consider:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Did they listen to your concerns?</li>
              <li>Did they explain things clearly?</li>
              <li>Do you feel comfortable with their approach?</li>
              <li>Do their suggestions make sense to you?</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Don't Hesitate to Ask Questions</h2>
            <p>Remember, this is your opportunity to ensure you're making the right choice. Don't hesitate to ask follow-up questions or request clarification on anything you're unsure about. A good practitioner will welcome your questions and be happy to explain their approach.</p>
          </div>

          <!-- AUTHOR BIO -->
          <div class="author-bio">
            <div class="bio-header">
